10/04/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The EU Rapid Reaction Force (EUFOR) and Macedonian Civil Aviation authorities have signed an agreement that allows EUFOR to use the country's airspace. At a news conference Wednesday (9 April), Maj Phillipe Soulie of the EU's Concordia mission stressed that forces are also ready to broadly engage in the campaign to collect illegally held weapons.
In other news Wednesday, Macedonian Deputy Prime Minister Radmila Sekerinska announced details of the annual draft-programme to harmonise domestic legislation with that of the EU. The government is expected to approve the programme in ten days. (MIA - 09/04/03)
